```jsx
// In your form component's render method
const { reset } = this.props;
<button type="button" onClick={reset}>Clear Form</button>
```
The `reset` prop is a function provided by `redux-form` that when called, reverts all form fields to their `initialValues`. `pristine` is a boolean flag indicating if the form has been modified from its initial state, and `submitting` is a boolean indicating if the form is currently being submitted.

```javascript
// React Hook Form minimizes re-renders on input change because it doesn't
// manage the input's value via React state directly on every keystroke.
const { register } = useForm();
<input {...register('name')} />
```

